495
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:08,020
How can you peek at my notebook?

496
00:29:08,780 --> 00:29:09,780
I didn't know whose notebook it was.

497
00:29:10,220 --> 00:29:11,940
Then you shouldn't have peeked at it.

498
00:29:12,260 --> 00:29:13,300
Since I didn't know whose it was,

499
00:29:13,300 --> 00:29:15,020
I needed to find out its owner

500
00:29:15,300 --> 00:29:16,220
and give it back.

501
00:29:18,220 --> 00:29:19,780
What have you read in it?

502
00:29:22,020 --> 00:29:23,020
What have I read in it?

503
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:28,220
I've read someone's will of making money

504
00:29:28,460 --> 00:29:30,180
and her ability of calculating.

505
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:32,020
I'm sure

506
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:33,620
she will get rich

507
00:29:33,620 --> 00:29:35,460
before her sixties.

508
00:29:37,060 --> 00:29:37,980
Su Wei'an,

509
00:29:38,220 --> 00:29:39,500
I'm starting to believe

510
00:29:39,500 --> 00:29:41,820
that you'd give up your doctor dream
to make money

511
00:29:43,740 --> 00:29:44,500
But,

512
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:47,500
giving up your dream for money,

513
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,500
isn't that a pale life?

514
00:29:56,460 --> 00:29:57,500
When we were in the operating room

515
00:29:58,820 --> 00:30:00,460
the way you held the flashlight

516
00:30:01,020 --> 00:30:02,420
made me feel like

517
00:30:02,420 --> 00:30:04,220
you were one of us.

518
00:30:07,820 --> 00:30:09,980
Su Wei'an, what are you thinking?

519
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:13,220
I still remember your words
while we were stargazing,

520
00:30:13,700 --> 00:30:15,460
"The sad light of a missing star

521
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:17,700
is just like our memories

522
00:30:17,900 --> 00:30:20,460
of a person who has passed away."

523
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:22,260
But I think,

524
00:30:23,180 --> 00:30:25,340
even if they're destined to die out,

525
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:27,300
the stars

526
00:30:27,300 --> 00:30:29,180
are still trying their best

527
00:30:29,460 --> 00:30:30,740
and devoting their whole power

528
00:30:31,180 --> 00:30:34,020
to shine in the sky.

529
00:30:34,260 --> 00:30:35,940
Just like each one of us,

530
00:30:37,020 --> 00:30:39,260
we're destined to pass away,

531
00:30:40,460 --> 00:30:43,100
but our lives hold value in this world,

532
00:30:43,580 --> 00:30:45,420
like the everlasting light of the stars

533
00:30:45,940 --> 00:30:47,020
shining in the sky.

534
00:30:53,980 --> 00:30:55,020
You're right, Mr. Gu.

535
00:30:55,740 --> 00:30:57,740
But I'm afraid I'll disappoint you.

536
00:30:58,020 --> 00:31:00,460
Making money is my only dream.

537
00:31:03,020 --> 00:31:05,500
Hopefully, with your blessing,

538
00:31:06,100 --> 00:31:07,820
I can live a pale life until my sixties.

539
00:31:18,460 --> 00:31:19,260
You're back.

540
00:31:23,820 --> 00:31:25,140
You must be tired.

541
00:31:28,300 --> 00:31:28,740
Come on,

542
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:30,100
I'll give you a massage.

543
00:31:31,860 --> 00:31:32,340
Come on.

544
00:31:35,450 --> 00:31:36,700
How's my strength?

545
00:31:36,860 --> 00:31:37,740
It's good.

546
00:31:42,780 --> 00:31:44,010
So comfortable.

547
00:31:46,180 --> 00:31:48,450
Take me with you when you go out,

548
00:31:49,010 --> 00:31:50,010
okay?

549
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:52,490
I can help share your burden,

550
00:31:54,700 --> 00:31:57,010
including the night snack.

551
00:31:59,180 --> 00:32:01,340
I guessed your real intention.

552
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:05,660
Today,

553
00:32:06,060 --> 00:32:07,450
if I didn't run into Dr. Gu
in the dining hall,

554
00:32:07,450 --> 00:32:09,060
I would have thought
you two were out together.

555
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:11,340
How could that be?

556
00:32:12,010 --> 00:32:14,340
He won't fancy me, you know.

557
00:32:14,450 --> 00:32:15,300
I don't know that.

558
00:32:16,220 --> 00:32:17,410
I even think

559
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:19,300
he has feelings for you.

560
00:32:20,780 --> 00:32:23,460
Aren't you special to him?

561
00:32:26,460 --> 00:32:27,140
Yes.

562
00:32:27,660 --> 00:32:28,500
Very special.

563
00:32:30,180 --> 00:32:30,900
Specially annoying.

564
00:32:31,780 --> 00:32:32,380
No,

565
00:32:33,020 --> 00:32:35,100
you didn't see his situation tonight.

566
00:32:35,540 --> 00:32:36,860
When I saw him tonight,

567
00:32:37,860 --> 00:32:40,500
he looks so lonely and vulnerable.

568
00:32:41,060 --> 00:32:42,700
It seems like he's longing for love.

569
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:43,300
Really.

570
00:32:43,780 --> 00:32:44,460
Why didn't I...?

571
00:32:47,140 --> 00:32:48,140
I mean,

572
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:50,380
